answers.answer: Looks good as far as it goes:  No diabetes (if this were a sample taken after fasting), no infection, no kidney disease.  Sample might not have been a clear mid-stream sampling (slight, inconsequential impurities) but perhaps it was.Does not appear to have been testing for pregnancy (hCG hormone level) imo.
Really? Omg I feel relieved :) thank youuuu <3
I believe the test results show that possibility was not part of the test.

I agree with scalpmassager.  This wasn't a pregnancy urinalysis.  I'm not sure what this was testing for,  besides maybe a bladder infection.  Whether or not you are pregnant wasn't tested in this urine test.If you haven't ever had sex,  though,  you aren't pregnant.
